He also offered insights into the operations of the Pakistani Taliban and the JuA.
Ehsan said the successful US-Afghan peace talks, which were facilitated by Pakistan, had served to further curtail Pakistani Taliban activity.
Later, he claimed responsibility on behalf of the Pakistani Taliban for killing journalists who were deemed to be "anti-Taliban".
"There was a lack of leadership, and people were very disappointed [with the Pakistani Taliban]," he said.
'Broken' agreements, easy escapesEhsan claims the agreement with Pakistani security forces granted him full legal immunity from any prosecution related to Pakistani Taliban or JuA attacks in addition to other privileges.